## MMS-Specific Test Scenarios

### TC001: App Launches Successfully

```
1. Run the app
   $ bun run dev

2. Wait for startup
   mcp__automation__sleep ms=3000

3. Screenshot
   mcp__automation__screenshot mode=full
   → Verify: App loads, canvas visible

4. Check console
   mcp__automation__type keys="LeftCommand,LeftOption,I"
   mcp__automation__sleep ms=500
   mcp__automation__screenshot mode=full
   → Verify: No red errors
```

### TC002: LOD Transitions (Macro → Meso → Micro)

```
1. Screenshot at default zoom
   mcp__automation__screenshot mode=full
   → Note which layer is active

2. Zoom out (scroll down)
   mcp__automation__mouseScroll direction="down" amount=5
   mcp__automation__sleep ms=500
   mcp__automation__screenshot mode=full
   → Verify: Macro layer (heatmap) visible

3. Zoom in (scroll up)
   mcp__automation__mouseScroll direction="up" amount=10
   mcp__automation__sleep ms=500
   mcp__automation__screenshot mode=full
   → Verify: Micro layer (HTML cards) visible

4. Check transitions are smooth, no flickering
```

### TC003: Sidebar Virtual Scroll Sync

```
1. Screenshot initial state
   mcp__automation__screenshot mode=full

2. Scroll sidebar down
   mcp__automation__mouseClick x=100 y=400  (sidebar area)
   mcp__automation__mouseScroll direction="down" amount=3

3. Screenshot result
   mcp__automation__screenshot mode=full
   → Verify: Canvas Y moved to match

4. Drag canvas
   mcp__automation__mouseDrag x=600 y=300  (from center)
   mcp__automation__mouseMove x=600 y=500

5. Screenshot
   mcp__automation__screenshot mode=full
   → Verify: Sidebar scroll position updated
```

### TC004: MicroLayer Accessibility

```
1. Zoom to Micro level

2. Tab through task cards
   mcp__automation__type keys="Tab"
   mcp__automation__screenshot mode=full
   → Verify: Focus indicator visible on card

3. Press Enter to select
   mcp__automation__type keys="Return"
   mcp__automation__screenshot mode=full
   → Verify: Card shows selected state

4. Check ARIA attributes in console
```

